rComments: Really good prof. She makes her expectations very clear and makes really good lectures/examples. If she emphasizes a certain type of question, you best believe it will show up on the midterm/final.

This is the fourth course I have taken with Rozalina. She is an amazing prof who wants her students to succeed and is always happy to clear up any problems you are having with the material. She also answers emails very quickly! Midterm/final reflect the material well, review assignments and lecture examples and you should be good to go.

Rozalina knows her stuff! She taught me 3 courses, geotech, hydraulics, and soils. She's much better than other profs teaching these courses. You need to pay attention in class. Do not skip tutorials and do the assignments and you will know exactly what to expect on the midterms/finals.
Rozalina is a great professor. She clearly writes down her examples on the board and explains them well. Highly recommend this professor.

Great prof. Very fair and very accessible via emails and office hours. Lectures are a little dry but she always does good examples. She will always post a review before the final and midterm and the material is always similar. I've had her for 3 classes already (3109, 3116 and 4108) and I have her again next semester (4184).

Good prof. She is very fair and professional. If you don't do well it's your fault because she puts up all the course material that you will need for the exams (with solutions), no surprises, you either know it or you don't. Her exams are very fair and will touch on all aspects of the class. Although her lectures are a bit dry.

Great prof! Knows her material inside out. You MUST attend her lectures, take notes and ask questions. Most people find her lecturing style very boring. If you can get past that then you will learn a lot from her. She is a very nice person and hates it when people talk in class. Her exams and midterms are fair and reflect on lecture notes.

She really opened up a lot more compared to the last time i took her class. She is helpful as always, and is really clear in terms of her grading. If you do the assignments, you should be good for the exams since the questions are very similar.  Her past experience as a geotechnical lab technician really shows in this soil mechanics class.

Great prof. Rozalina is extremely nice and her exams are extremely fair. She taught Hydraulics which is usually a hard class, but she made it much easier because her exams actually reflected the material, assignments and reviews. Her grading is very forgiving. She is always happy when you go see her for help, and is very understanding.  Take her!
Very boring to listen to, but tests fair. 3116 assignments were no joke.
Very professional, knows her stuff and gives great feedback. Helped me a lot during the whole course. Her lectures were very detailed and had everything I needed to know for the test.

Very nice and very accommodating professor.  helps out alot, midterms and finals are very clear and it is what you see in the lectures and she always gives a review before the final and midterm to show you what to expect and she provides questions in the exams almost replica of the review! very fair very nice person!

Great professor, she is clear and throughly prepares her classes. Considering the amount of courses she had for this semester , she was quite available to answer to your questions. Her expectations were cristal clear and she gives you everything(even the "solved in class" examples).

Fairly good prof, boring lecturer especially from 7pm-10pm on Wednesday nights, midterm & final exam were very similar to the review lecture she gave beforehand, not a hard class with her but not the most interesting you will take in 4th year, assignments are optional (weight shift to final if not handed in) and there is a group project at the end

I see level of helfulness and I dont understand why. But she always been rude to me for no reason everytime I ask a question or when I go see her. And im not a bad student. Im always sitting in the front and never distrubing. I passed the class with A only because the TAs were always open to help. So sad

Amazing at answering questions by email or during office hour. All my questions were answered clearly and efficiently. HOWEVER, she is VERY boring during lectures.  Her lectures feel like she is talking to a camera, it doesn't feel like she is talking to us. The tone is very professional but boring as hell. Insightful. Helpful. Nice. but BORING.
